- I'm lost.

14:29.169 --> 14:34.372
I gave my entire life
to my career,
and I make one mistake,

14:34.441 --> 14:39.443
<i> And now I'm awaiting</i>
<i> disciplinary action while</i>
<i> someone else sits at my desk.</i>

14:39.479 --> 14:41.245
<i> And what's almost worse</i>

14:41.281 --> 14:45.383
Is that I thought I was close
to my coworkers,
like, really close.

14:45.452 --> 14:47.051
I thought I was a mentor.

14:47.120 --> 14:49.387
<i>Since I left, I barely see them.</i>

14:49.456 --> 14:52.990
<i> People at work,</i>
<i> especially the women,</i>
<i> they're like my family,</i>

14:53.026 --> 14:57.662
And I miss them,
and I'm not sure I know who I am
without them.

14:58.198 --> 14:59.530
- Hey.

15:01.201 --> 15:03.401
The fried pigeon...

15:03.536 --> 15:05.670
Will not just fly
into your mouth.

15:07.207 --> 15:09.006
- Uh, come again?

15:09.042 --> 15:11.943
- You want change,
you work for it.

15:12.078 --> 15:14.345
Get out of bed,
put on your clothes,

15:14.347 --> 15:16.214
Answer those phone calls,
stop moping!

15:16.349 --> 15:19.550
Luckily for you, I can help.
But first,

15:19.552 --> 15:21.118
At your work,

15:21.187 --> 15:25.122
You're replaced
by an inferior man,
am I right?

15:26.626 --> 15:30.762
- So pink cocaine has recently
been purchased here,
here and here.

15:30.897 --> 15:33.398
- So distribution didn't die
with will french.

15:33.533 --> 15:36.500
- No, but if we comb
through these hotspots,

15:36.536 --> 15:40.237
Perhaps we can figure out
who the new local supplier is.

15:40.239 --> 15:43.507
- How?
- Well...
I have created an algorithm

15:43.543 --> 15:45.843
That uses pre-existing
drug-arrest stats

15:45.879 --> 15:48.713
To show average physical
proximity down to the kilometre

15:48.715 --> 15:50.648
Between dealers
and their local suppliers.

15:50.717 --> 15:54.719
- Isn't that basically
geographic profiling?
Used to find serial killers?

15:54.788 --> 15:57.188
- Yes, but it's never been used
to find drug suppliers before,

15:57.257 --> 15:59.857
And apprehend them
before they get more product
onto the streets.

15:59.893 --> 16:02.593
- Kind of like minority report,
but for drugs.

16:02.729 --> 16:04.529
- I'm not sure
what you're saying,

16:04.664 --> 16:07.331
I'm just saying I want
to anticipate crime and stop it
before it happens.

16:09.869 --> 16:14.272
- Right. But...
Don't we think the stats
can be a little biased?

16:14.274 --> 16:16.741
- It's called intelligence-led
policing, greene.

16:16.743 --> 16:18.709
That's what we're doing today,
okay?

16:18.778 --> 16:21.812
So pull the data on any dealer
from these areas,

16:21.848 --> 16:24.148
Input it,
let the computer do the rest.

16:24.283 --> 16:27.451
(knocking)
excuse me.

16:32.425 --> 16:34.191
(humming)

16:34.861 --> 16:36.694
(inhaling and gasping)

16:36.829 --> 16:38.496
- It's as I suspected.

16:39.499 --> 16:42.699
Both you and your son...
Are cursed.

16:42.736 --> 16:45.302
<i> But I have just the thing</i>
<i> to help.</i>

16:45.338 --> 16:49.373
Magic spring water
from egerszalók, hungary.

16:50.343 --> 16:51.876
