- What the hell?
- That kid is definitely
underage.

31:59.885 --> 32:03.086
- Oh... God, I gotta stop,
I gotta stop, I gotta stop.

32:03.155 --> 32:06.556
- Why does adeline have this?
(sam and kelly):
She's blackmailing him.

32:06.592 --> 32:09.893
- This is how she got the cartel
to supply the coyotes
the pink cocaine.

32:09.895 --> 32:13.096
Sell me your drugs,
or I tell your macho friends
that you like teenage boys.

32:13.231 --> 32:16.767
- So adeline made the cartel
connect, but will's controlling
everything?

32:16.902 --> 32:19.502
- Explains why she felt entitled
to take over.

32:19.538 --> 32:23.173
- Let's press zorka.
Get her to contact adeline now.

32:24.476 --> 32:26.843
- Balda, I need your help.

32:26.912 --> 32:28.911
Come to the fair now.

32:30.582 --> 32:32.782
There. I left her a message.

32:32.818 --> 32:35.786
It was the place that her father
picked for emergencies.

32:35.921 --> 32:38.789
- You sure adeline's getting
these voicemails?
- Yes.

32:38.924 --> 32:40.590
(phone chiming)
(scoffing)
see?

32:40.592 --> 32:42.793
The smile,
it means she's coming.

32:42.795 --> 32:44.527
- Give me the phone back.

32:44.563 --> 32:47.464
- What if there's an emergency?
- Give me the--

32:47.466 --> 32:50.933
- You need anything,
you just talk into this.
Testing, testing.

32:50.970 --> 32:52.536
Okay, good to go.

32:52.671 --> 32:54.338
- And don't worry,
we'll have eyes on you.

32:54.473 --> 32:56.673
Detectives duff and wazowski
will keep an eye out
for adeline.

32:56.808 --> 32:58.708
Come on,
let's get you into position.

33:01.080 --> 33:03.680
(children laughing)
(fairground music playing)

33:09.955 --> 33:11.555
(cheering)

33:14.493 --> 33:17.828
- This is all a little weird.
- Yup!

33:17.963 --> 33:19.595
<i> (naz): See adeline yet?</i>

33:20.866 --> 33:23.900
- No. Nothing but the butt
of a dinosaur.

33:23.969 --> 33:25.769
- It's called a cloaca,
actually.

33:25.838 --> 33:29.639
It's a three-in-one orifice
and... It do-doesn't matter.

33:30.509 --> 33:32.208
- What's wrong with you today?

33:33.979 --> 33:37.781
- Uh... Do you know that you are
standing behind a historically
inaccurate dinosaur?

33:37.783 --> 33:39.516
The brontosauri actually
never existed.

33:39.651 --> 33:43.253
You know, you spend a long time
believing something
and then bam!

33:43.255 --> 33:45.455
Everything you knew
just isn't true.

33:47.459 --> 33:49.692
(bell ringing)

33:49.762 --> 33:53.129
(sighing)
- she's not coming.
I have a bad feeling.

33:53.265 --> 33:55.665
Balda,
she only thinks of herself.

33:55.667 --> 33:57.934
- Alright, sit tight.
We'll give it
a few more minutes.

34:11.216 --> 34:14.117
- Where the hell is she?
Dammit, let's go!

34:16.021 --> 34:19.356
- Yeah, we lost zorka.
<i> Checking the southeast side</i>
<i> of the mall!</i>

34:19.358 --> 34:21.892
- Got it. We'll go northwest.
Let's go.

34:21.894 --> 34:24.894
- Ugh! Where'd she go?
- I don't know, I don't see her!

34:28.233 --> 34:31.501
- Oh, eyes on zorka!
She's with a man, blue shirt,
by the brontosaurus!

34:31.636 --> 34:33.370
- Brachiosaurus!
- Ugh!

34:33.372 --> 34:37.940
(dinging)
- no, no, no, no, no, no, no!
(train whistle blowing)

34:41.547 --> 34:43.479
Come on, move!

34:43.515 --> 34:45.582
(soft french music)

34:47.519 --> 34:49.119
- Hey, here!

34:59.598 --> 35:00.797
- Come on!

35:09.675 --> 35:12.074
Let's go!
(groaning and panting)

35:14.580 --> 35:17.313
Excuse me!
- Go, go, go! Excuse me!

35:20.619 --> 35:23.019
(zorka crying out and groaning)

35:30.462 --> 35:32.696
(train whistle blowing)

35:32.831 --> 35:34.931
- Go, go, go.

35:38.470 --> 35:41.103
(kelly): Hey! Sam, this way!

35:43.775 --> 35:46.176
- Stop!
- Stop! Police!

35:49.481 --> 35:51.914
(grunting)

35:53.318 --> 35:55.618
- Gtpd! Get your hands
behind your back!

35:55.654 --> 35:58.054
- Balda sent them to take me.

35:58.090 --> 36:02.058
- Take you?
You paid me 500 bucks
to get you outta there.

36:02.094 --> 36:06.395
- No. No, no, no. Mm-mm.

36:08.600 --> 36:10.500
(police-radio chatter)

36:11.803 --> 36:14.371
- So dude over here says
he doesn't even know adeline.

36:14.373 --> 36:17.941
- Yeah, and zorka says
she never gave him any money.
- So who do we believe?

36:17.943 --> 36:20.877
Bad guy ride-share
or snake oil saleswoman?

36:22.648 --> 36:26.082
Well, adelina's a nightmare,
but she's still the only family
zorka's got left,

36:26.151 --> 36:28.952
And she's still the strongest
lead in our coyote case.

36:29.021 --> 36:32.655
- Okay, so where the hell
is adeline?

36:34.459 --> 36:37.627
- I hope you all had a chance
to finish reading the haunting
of chauncey dubois,

36:37.629 --> 36:40.563
Because there will be
some spoilers!

36:40.632 --> 36:44.034
- Spoilers as in rotten?
Because I tried to read it,

36:44.169 --> 36:47.170
But it stinks!
Don't you guys...

36:47.305 --> 36:50.073
Think... Think so?

36:50.208 --> 36:53.910
- Uh, so anyone want to try
my bean salad?

36:54.880 --> 36:57.647
- So anyway, the other day,

36:57.649 --> 36:59.783
I was playing with my cat,
cloudy -

36:59.918 --> 37:03.253
He's the scottish fold
with the bladder crystals -
when all of a sudden,

37:03.322 --> 37:08.057
His favourite cat toy started
to sway all on its own.

37:09.461 --> 37:12.628
I wasn't moving it,
and cloudy certainly
wasn't moving it!

37:13.799 --> 37:15.465
And I was wondering,

37:15.600 --> 37:18.735
Maybe it was the air
conditioner!
But it's broken!

37:18.870 --> 37:20.836
Not that my landlord cares.
(chuckling)

37:22.641 --> 37:25.208
- Do any of us really care?
(guffawing)

37:25.210 --> 37:28.478
(woman): Okay, who here
has slept with their landlord?

37:28.547 --> 37:31.080
(sighing)
(woman): Huh?
(laughing)

37:37.322 --> 37:40.289
(door opening)
- oh, hey, hi! Come on in.

37:40.325 --> 37:42.425
What a nice surprise.
She's in there.

37:42.427 --> 37:44.093
- Okay.

37:44.129 --> 37:47.563
- Sam! What are you doing here?
- Oh, well, the lights were on,

37:47.565 --> 37:51.301
I was passing by and I was,
like: "hey, I'll just..."
that's a lie.

37:57.843 --> 38:00.676
I just wanted to talk
about the other day with zorka.

38:02.380 --> 38:05.848
- What about it?
- Uh, the whole thing
about us being family,

38:05.884 --> 38:08.218
And then you feeling lost
and neglected because...

38:08.353 --> 38:11.321
We didn't come by
to check on you.

38:12.557 --> 38:14.991
(chuckling, then laughing)

38:16.328 --> 38:19.395
- I was acting.
I had to give her something.

38:20.198 --> 38:22.131
- Sounded true.

38:24.402 --> 38:26.402
- Oh, sam. Sam...

38:26.438 --> 38:28.872
Ah! Come on.

38:30.876 --> 38:34.143
I'm fine.
Yeah, I'm a little bored,

38:34.212 --> 38:38.348
A lot frustrated,
but... I'm fine.

38:38.483 --> 38:40.149
- Good.

38:44.189 --> 38:45.821
- Liz? Elizabeth!

38:47.326 --> 38:50.626
Kevin, he-he's... He's walking,
he's eating.
What'd you give him?

38:50.662 --> 38:54.029
- Nothing,
other than that water.

38:54.066 --> 38:55.932
(gasping)

38:55.934 --> 38:57.433
- Mm...

38:59.271 --> 39:01.671
- Night, judy.
- Michaela.
(fake laugh)

39:04.442 --> 39:07.376
- "so my scottish fold
said to my air conditioner,

39:07.412 --> 39:09.112
'maybe we're both haunted.' "

39:09.181 --> 39:12.515
- I think you are gonna be
haunted by michaela's bean salad
tonight.

39:12.584 --> 39:15.918
I've never seen someone pretend
to enjoy legumes so much.

39:15.987 --> 39:19.722
- Well, what can I say?
I'm really good at pretending.

39:19.725 --> 39:22.058
- Yeah?
- Pretending to like things,

39:22.060 --> 39:24.059
Pretending to be someone
I'm not.

39:25.263 --> 39:27.864
- Why is that?
- My mother never approved
of me.

39:29.334 --> 39:32.001
If she could've chosen
a different daughter,
she would've.

39:32.003 --> 39:35.138
- I think that's how my daughter
feels about me.
- But you guys live together,

39:35.140 --> 39:37.540
Right? You're not... Close?

39:37.576 --> 39:41.010
- Well, I try to be,
but sam's never here. She's a...

39:41.079 --> 39:43.079
She's a cop. Total workaholic.

39:43.081 --> 39:45.682
(sighing)
obsessed with this new case.

39:45.684 --> 39:47.951
- Ooh! True crime!
- Mm.

39:48.086 --> 39:50.954
Although I bet
you can't really tell me
about it, though, right?

39:51.089 --> 39:52.822
- Well, I don't really know
that much,

39:52.957 --> 39:56.959
But she thinks
this real-estate agent's
overdose was actually a murder.

39:56.995 --> 39:59.262
H-honestly, I don't know.
(laughing)

39:59.264 --> 40:01.364
- Well...

40:01.433 --> 40:05.168
If my mother would rather
a different daughter,

40:05.170 --> 40:08.638
And your daughter would rather
a different mother, then maybe
they don't deserve us.

40:08.640 --> 40:10.406
- Maybe they don't.

40:10.442 --> 40:12.175
- Good night, new mommy.
(laughter)

40:12.244 --> 40:14.710
- Good night, sweetie.
- Will I see you soon?

40:14.712 --> 40:16.379
- Absolutely.

40:17.015 --> 40:18.814
(chuckling)

40:19.885 --> 40:21.951
(sighing)

40:23.221 --> 40:24.820
(door opening)

40:27.659 --> 40:29.291
- Hi.
(kelly chuckling)

40:30.261 --> 40:32.128
You forget something, or...

40:32.263 --> 40:35.531
- Uh, no. I...

40:35.667 --> 40:38.000
Actually wanted to talk to you.
Um...

40:40.005 --> 40:41.738
(sighing)

40:41.873 --> 40:45.875
I know I haven't been
very supportive,
or at all supportive, really.

40:47.012 --> 40:48.577
(sighing)

40:50.182 --> 40:52.348
I'm happy for you guys.

40:53.618 --> 40:56.151
It's just...
(sighing)

40:56.188 --> 40:58.621
...Not the easiest thing for me
to show up for.

40:58.756 --> 41:03.293
- Why?
- Because... I want a baby too.

41:05.330 --> 41:08.965
It's like this emptiness inside.
(sighing)

41:10.935 --> 41:13.570
- Well, are you sure you want
a baby? 'cause it kind of sounds
like you want to eat a baby.

41:13.572 --> 41:16.172
(kelly chuckling)
maybe you should've had
more cake.

41:16.174 --> 41:17.773
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

41:17.809 --> 41:21.377
I guess you don't know what
it feels like to be jealous...

41:21.379 --> 41:22.979
Miss perfect.

41:23.048 --> 41:25.247
- Oh, miss perfect?
- Yeah.
- Oh.

41:25.283 --> 41:29.118
May I remind you that
I'm having this baby on my own?

41:29.120 --> 41:31.287
It's far from what I wanted.

41:32.790 --> 41:35.391
And believe it or not,
I was jealous of you
when we were kids.

41:35.393 --> 41:38.728
Yes, you were my confident,
funny-as-hell sister

41:38.797 --> 41:40.730
That all of my friends
wanted to be friends with,

41:40.799 --> 41:43.132
And all of my crushes
wanted to date.

41:43.201 --> 41:47.870
- Let's be clear, okay?
At home, I was the underdog,
like, dead last.

41:47.873 --> 41:49.739
- Well, then try putting
yourself first for once.

41:49.808 --> 41:53.343
That's why I'm doing this
on my own.
I am putting what I want first.

41:53.478 --> 41:56.679
So hey, if there's something
that you want,

41:56.681 --> 41:58.681
Go get it.

41:58.816 --> 42:00.749
You have one life, right?

42:00.785 --> 42:03.019
(phone buzzing)

42:03.021 --> 42:04.820
- Yeah.

42:04.856 --> 42:06.356
- It's okay, get it.

42:08.093 --> 42:10.493
(sighing)
you're a cop,
answer your goddamn phone.

42:10.562 --> 42:12.161
- Okay, okay, okay.

42:14.699 --> 42:16.298
Hey, nathan.

42:18.436 --> 42:20.436
Okay.

42:20.438 --> 42:22.438
I'll be right there. Yeah.

42:24.576 --> 42:26.141
(sighing)

42:27.012 --> 42:29.312
- I love you.
- I love you.

42:29.314 --> 42:30.913
And I love you.

42:30.949 --> 42:33.415
- Yes. Go.
- Bye! Okay!

42:37.722 --> 42:39.455
What's going on?

42:39.457 --> 42:41.924
- Adeline french's evidence
files have been scrambled.

42:41.993 --> 42:45.194
- What?
- All the photos,
everything on the drive: Gone.

42:45.263 --> 42:48.931
- But the drive was in evidence.
Only police had access to it.
- Exactly.

42:51.303 --> 42:54.870
- So adeline has someone inside
covering her tracks.

42:54.940 --> 42:57.273
- Which means the oce
has a dirty cop.

42:59.277 --> 43:02.211
- Michaels is losing it
right now.
He's locking everything down.

43:02.247 --> 43:04.013
I wanted you to know, alright?

43:04.015 --> 43:06.849
- Greene. My office. Now.

